ow this has been ranted on....I don't care!<br>You have a pet control it! You can't control it DON&quot;t make a new one right after you've gotten rezzed becuase your last one was brecking the mezzers spells!<br>I know it's possible to work with the enchie and still have a pet. I&quot;VE DONE IT!!! There have been times when my groups gotten almost run over by 12+mobs and so each of us gets hit which, means my pet starts going berserk on one and everybody else is trying to help the MA.<br>Enchie AE mezes and pet breaks one, I have a hot key for pet back off and an enchie usually only has to throw on or 2 messes on a mob while i get my pet t calm down. If that doesn't work I tel the enchie to stop and throw my own mez up then tell them when it breaks. Thus they don't waste mana, have pet break mez and then get bashed on. Hell I've destroyed my pet becuase it was bing a dick!<br>So don't @#%$ make a new right after you died! If it @#%$ attacking something I'm trying to mez...HIDE, GO INVIS...but get that pet off the mob!<br>Weak I know, but pisses me off when others can't control pets properly.<br>P.S. Don't die from a mob we told you not to kill, and then make a new pet and attack the mob with it....we won't help you!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usakkathdeath1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sakkathdeath1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 169<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/19/02 9:27:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3183.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pets on raids</span><hr size=1> As a pet class (and someone who can handle their pet well IMO), it annoys me no end when people give pets a bad name by not controling theirs properly. Pets are already not welcome on a lot of raid situations due to pathing/level aggro problems, having people who can't control them indicate to the whole raid how bad they <i>can</i> be if mishandled does us even further disservice.<br><br>I think pet users should have to pass an exam, with a practical element before they're allowed their next pet spell! That will leave only those capable of proper control in the hands of such deadly weapons.<br><br>All it takes is a few people screwing up to create the illusion that pets are just bad news. Rumours spread and stay engraved in peoples mind - like the old DoT bug that (was fixed years ago) used to make corpses poof, and I've still been on many raids where DoTs are not permitted for this purpose (ie on big mobs - not because of mezzing issues). <p><select name="Characters" style="font-size: 12; font-family: verdana, arial; color: #80ffff; background-color: black;"><br><option selected>Sakkath D'Eath, 56 Defiler and Guild Leader of Contagion<br><option>Shubb, 45 Druid<br></select><br><br><img src=http://www.wecomm.com/check/sakk.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/upyrastilia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pyrastilia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 404<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/19/02 10:00:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3183.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> In some situations pets are just impossible to control (several AE casting mobs, mobs that charm or fear, etc...) so generally it's best just to say 'no pets' on raids.  They cause more trouble than they're worth.<br><br>Pyra <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uk1ssk1ng.showPublicProfile?language=EN>K1SSK1nG</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 886<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/19/02 10:44:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3183.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> i used to have a &quot;one strike&quot; policy when i led raids, when dealing with pets. One mistake and your pet privilege is gone. for an unknown amount of time (depending on how skillful you are from then on). It got so bad i just said the hell with it and only let one person use pets, Visnet...the only mage i've ever seen control a pet flawlessly. <p><a href="http://www.selectsmart.com/FREE/select.php3?client=fffemale789what" target="_blank"><img src="http://rainecloud910.freewebspace.com/Selphieuse.jpg"></a><br>Which female character from Final Fantasy 7,8,9 are you?? <p align left>Go find out <a href="http://www.selectsmart.com/FREE/select.php3?client=fffemale789what" target="_blank">here</a>! made by <lj user=rainecloud></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulateris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lateris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/19/02 10:53:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3183.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pets on raids</span><hr size=1> &quot;an enchie usually only has to throw on or 2 messes on a mob while i get my pet t calm down.&quot;<br><br>  More often than not One mezz is all you get ,a break means enchie beat down , or throws the enchie off becuase he\she has to deal with the broken m