.com/usyldramarlowe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syldra Marlowe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/19/02 11:03:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3183.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> In my experiences I do one of two things on our raids... 1. allow pets at the owner's discretion.  (If there is ANY problems with pet the privalage is taken away from the entire raid) 2. allow no pets... just for the sake of sanity.<br><br>Depends on where we're raiding, who's with us, and if we can really benefit from the extra damage.<br><br>I have to also add that I am very impressed by most people who raid with pet classes.  Those who I feel confident about are the same ones who double check to see if its ok to use pets on the raids rather than just strike it up and send it in. <p>Syldra Marlowe 52 Vicar<br>Guild Leader ~ <a href="http://pub64.ezboard.com/bsacrummortis">Sacrum Mortis</a><br><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=114107">Syldra's Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uyendar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yendar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/19/02 11:40:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3183.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pets on raids</span><hr size=1> As a pet owner I just have to reply to this.<br><br>Knowing when to use pets and when to get rid of them is the key.  If I am in a group that